See More
See Less



Author Information
Christopher G. Worley is Senior Research Scientist at the
University of Southern California’s Center for Effective
Organizations. He is also professor of management at Pepperdine
University’s Graziadio School of Business and Management.
Thomas Williams is a Senior Executive Advisor at
Strategy& (formerly Booz & Company) where he consults to
large global companies on issues of strategy, organization, and
management systems.
Edward E. Lawler III is Director of the Center for
Effective Organizations at the University of Southern California
and Distinguished Professor of Management and Organization in the
USC Marshall School of Business.


